summary:
Proven capabilities to create and develop business ideas from start-up to full-scale. Proactive global mindset with multi-cultural experience developed in Europe, the Middle East, and Africa.

Mehmed Mehmedov is best known as a founder of ALBADIRA Companies in Turkey and Bulgaria and KINALI Tourism – one of the leading travel agencies in M.I.C.E. tourism in Istanbul.

Mehmed was born in 1980 and was raised in Razgrad/Bulgaria. When he was nine years old his family migrated to Istanbul. After graduating with a degree of B.A. in Tourism Management from Bogazici University, Mehmed started to work as a Foreign Trade Specialist in Istanbul. Parallel with his first job, Mehmed enrolled to Bogazici University Certificate Program and become a Certified Foreign Trade Specialist.

After working in different companies for six years, driven by its entrepreneurial spirit, Mehmed founded his first company ALBADIRA (Turkey) in Istanbul and get a license for group "A" tour operator under the name "KINALI Tourism" at the age of 30. The main business focus of Mehmed was on foreign trade & tourism. One year later in 2011, Mehmed founded ALBADIRA (Bulgaria) – a company specialized in international trading and agricultural & real estate investment.

In October 2014, Mehmed co-founded SAVITA Invest - a fast growing property development company based in Plovdiv, specialized in the acquisition and development of residential properties in Bulgaria.

Currently, Mehmed is engaged  in leveraging smart data for business success...
